results.notes: All fields up to offset 35 (version, reserved0, filestoreCapacity, reserved1, currentMaxLogSize, currentLogSize, entryCount, oldestYear, oldestMonth, oldestDay, oldestHour, oldestMinute, oldestSecond, reserved2) match perfectly between the canonical definition and the PDF table. The message class_id, message_id, and message_type also match. The discrepancy is that the PDF's 'Payload description' table on page 2 is truncated and does not list all fields for the full 48-byte payload, which the canonical definition correctly describes. This is a common occurrence in u-blox manuals where tables might be abbreviated or refer to an older version of the message.

The canonical definition matches the Class ID (0x21), Message ID (0x08), and total payload length (48 bytes) specified in the PDF manual for UBX-LOG-INFO (Log information). All fields explicitly listed in the PDF manual (up to 'newestYear' at byte offset 36) match the canonical definition in terms of name, byte offset, data type, and description. The PDF manual's payload description table truncates after 'newestYear', but the canonical definition correctly accounts for the remaining 10 bytes (offsets 38-47) by including 'newestMonth', 'newestDay', 'newestHour', 'newestMinute', 'newestSecond', 'reserved3', 'status', and 'reserved4', which perfectly fit the 48-byte payload length.
